synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involves placing 500 mg of a glass-ceramic sulfide solid electrolyte material (Li2S-P2S5-LiI) into a sealed container in a glove box filled with Ar gas, introducing 17.5 cc of oxygen gas, heating the container in an electric furnace at 210Â°C for 5000 seconds to produce a sulfide solid electrolyte material.
